      "writtenOn": "2020-07-28T14:20:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good question. It\u0027s from lessons learned in the python implementation.\n\nThe job in G3 looks at storage to know when to trigger canary rolls. Whenever there is a new file it triggers a run.\nWithout this check what used to happen is that if a bot times out, or dies for whatever reason, then it used to trigger a new run. When things went very wrong, new tasks kept getting triggered for the same patchset+cl (even though they were already running), making the G3 job blow up.\nWith this check we ensure that as long as the G3 job is still running a task we do not needlessly keep retriggering it. I had also thought of adding something on the G3 job side instead, but this was just way easier.",
      "parentUuid": "9b5a3f28_bb25fcfd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 78
      },
      "revId": "0013742fe8c00a6f2c2ed87bc462fa85c430fd30",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
